benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search/{searchKey} - Search custom fields

covered: Valid GET Requests: The test suite covers happy-path GET with required path parameter and multiple valid parameter combinations (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC29).
Empty Response: Tests verify 200 with empty array when no matches exist (TC06).
Pagination and Limits: Tests cover limit/offset, boundary limits and multi-page retrieval (TC02, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC28).
Query Parameters and Robustness: Tests cover valid/invalid param values (limit, offset, audit), and extra parameters ignored (TC10, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14).
Authorization: Tests cover missing and invalid tokens (TC15, TC16).
Error Handling and Bad Input: 400 responses for malformed/invalid inputs (TC11-14) and invalid audit value (TC14).
Availability and Resilience: 503 service unavailability (TC17) and 405 method not allowed (TC30).
Security and Input Validation: XSS/injection test (TC18) and Unicode/edge cases (TC27, TC26) and large payloads (TC19).
Performance and Concurrency: Stress test (TC19) and concurrent requests (TC20).
Integration and Compatibility: Data consistency with dependent services (TC23) and backward compatibility (TC22).
Documentation and Error Messages: API docs/readiness and descriptive errors (TC24).
Regression and Defaults: Handling of empty searchKey (TC21) and default parameter values (TC29).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling behavior under high request load.
Caching Behavior: No tests asserting caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or caching strategy.
Authorization Scope: No tests differentiating 401 vs 403 responses or permission-based restrictions beyond missing/invalid tokens.
Internal Server Errors: No explicit test for 500-level backend/database failures beyond 503 service unavailability (e.g., simulated DB failure).
recommendations: Add rate-limiting and throttling tests to verify behavior under burst traffic (expect 429 or proper handling).
Add caching tests to validate caching headers and invalidation behavior (ETag/If-None-Match, Cache-Control).
Add tests for permission-related failures (403) in addition to 401 for authentication.
Add tests for 500 Internal Server Errors to cover unexpected backend failures beyond 503.
